title: White House restricts U.S. investment in some Chinese tech, citing national security concerns
description: An official said the executive order is carefully focused so as not to stifle business between the world's two largest economies.

title: UPS CEO says drivers will average $170,000 in pay and benefits at end of 5-year deal
description: UPS and the Teamsters Union reached a tentative agreement late last month, averting a strike.

title: FBI shoots and kills Utah man wanted for threats against Biden, Manhattan DA
description: Court documents say the man shot by the FBI in Utah, Craig Deleeuw Robertson, was seen wearing a Trump hat.

title: Thursday's inflation data may be low, but don't expect the Fed to declare 'mission accomplished' yet
description: History has shown that inflation is stubborn and can last longer than expected.

title: 'This is going to get worse before it gets better': Panama Canal pileup due to drought reaches 154 vessels
description: Ongoing drought conditions and Panama Canal restrictions due to lower water levels are causing massive shipping congestion at the key trade gateway.

title: Disney set to report earnings after the bell. Here's what to expect
description: Investors are looking for more clarity on how Iger plans to fix Disney's TV business and juggle the decline of subscribers at Disney+.

title: I was shocked at how many one-star ratings I have on Uber — here's how to see yours
description: Your Uber app can show you how your Uber score breaks down, including how many one-star reviews drivers have given you.

title: Roblox shares drop 20% after company misses estimates on top and bottom line
description: Roblox reported its second-quarter results Wednesday.

title: These charts show what has Moody’s worried about regional banks including U.S. Bank and Fifth Third
description: The Moody's downgrade of 10 banks this week and warnings that more could be coming reignited concerns over U.S. regional banks.

title: Obesity drug Wegovy's landmark trial result could 'open up' health insurance access, analyst says
description: Popular weight-loss drug Wegovy could be made available under more health insurance schemes after the results of a late-stage trial pointed to the drug's efficacy in reducing cardiovascular events, analysts said Wednesday.

title: Italian bank stocks rebound as government waters down windfall tax
description: Italian bank shares rebounded on Wednesday after the government watered down a surprise windfall tax on excess profits announced earlier this week.

title: Sony first-quarter profit falls 31% but sales beat expectations on PlayStation 5 boost
description: Sony on Wednesday reported a 31% fall in profit in June quarter on weakness in its life insurance unit — but solid gaming performance drove a bump in revenues.

title: China hawk says Beijing could attack Taiwan by 2024, bringing ‘war to the West’
description: Prominent China hawk Kyle Bass told CNBC Tuesday that he believes Chinese President Xi Jinping is determined to "bring war to the West," with an invasion of Taiwan likely by 2024.

title: China reports smaller-than-expected drop in consumer prices
description: Lackluster domestic demand has persisted since the pandemic.

title: Forget ‘quiet quitting’ — ‘loud laborers’ are killing workplace morale. Here’s how to spot them
description: 'Loud laborers' are employees who place more emphasis on making their work known, rather than "focusing on the work itself," said workplace expert Nicole Price.

title: Indian automaker Mahindra says competition from Tesla 'does not faze us'
description: Anish Shah, the managing director and CEO of the Mahindra Group, said the company isn't worried about global competition in India's Electric Vehicle market, including Tesla.
